message.content: Most women in Barbados have a negative perception of divorce. They generally view it as a last resort and believe that marriage should be a lifelong commitment. Women in Barbados prioritize maintaining a stable and harmonious family unit, and divorce is often seen as a disruption to this ideal. They may perceive divorce as a failure or a sign of personal and societal shortcomings. However, attitudes towards divorce may vary among individuals based on their personal experiences and circumstances.
